Defendant Shawn T Witt in court, in custody, with attorney Donna Jean Kuchler.   Lesli S Boese appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Court reviews with the Atty's the Presentence Report.  

Sentencing argument by Atty. Boese.  Statement by Jean S.  Sentencing argument by Atty. Kuchler  Statements by defendant.  

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed Sentence of:

67 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 817 days )
- 47 Years of Initial Confinement
- 20 Years of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Courses for Cognitive Change and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge;
-No contact with Virgina Redlin, Thomas Redlin, Jean Stafford, Karalee Volenti, Karisa Fendl, Debra Moll, Janice Doerr, Scott Brook, Matthew Barker, Alice Anibas and Dorothy Anibas .

Restitution: $600 to Crime Victims Compensation (to be paid through no more than 25% of prison funds)

Cost: $ 368.00
DNA surcharge: $250.00
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
To be paid after restitution is paid and  hrough no more than 25% of prison funds

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program
